Our team of talented and determined individuals, are endlessly driven by our core values: Empowered by Innovation, We Make It Happen, Family and Brutally Honest. We take pride in our work, people, and dedication to quality, every step of the way. Apply today if you are qualified applicant looking for a challenging and rewarding career!

Jr. Business Intelligence Analyst
The Junior Business Intelligence Analyst will work closely with the team in supporting all business intelligence related-maters, including technical support, system maintenance, data analysis, and ad-hoc report. Duties and responsibilities include but are not limited to the following:

Education
Post-secondary education in Computer Science, Business Intelligence, Accounting, Finance, or related studies.
Years of Experience
1 Year
Working Conditions
Hours of Operation: 8:30 AM - 5:00 PM
Junior Level
Advanced level in MS Office 365 (Excel, Macros, PowerPoint, Visio, and SharePoint);
Intermediate level in Business Intelligence Tools (Power BI, Power Query, DAX, and Power Automate);
Strong SQL Skills (Queries, Views, Stored Procedure);
Knowledge of one of the data analysis programming languages (Python, R) is an asset;
Knowledge in ERP system and Crystal Report Writer is an asset;
Demonstrates initiative, diligence, a positive attitude and a willingness to learn;
Attention to detail and accuracy is required;
Create and maintain BI documentation for all processes and related data dictionary, design logic, flowchart, and user manual;
Assist in stakeholder management, build and maintain strong working relationships with internal and external stakeholders;
Effectively communicate issues, actively engage, influence, and work collaboratively as a team member;
Professional and tact to handle confidential information and;
Demonstrate State's core values and work in a team environment.
Job Specific Duties
Assist in all stages of a business intelligence life cycle, including SOP documentation, system maintenance, and routine report;
Manage help desk tickets, provide technical support to users and perform troubleshooting on system support;
Assist in the data extraction, cleaning, analysis, and create ad-hoc report;
Support and maintain the corporate intranet website and the automated workflows;
Maintain security access control, create the user account, and provide ERP administrative assistance;
Assist in system implementation, integration service, and training support;
Any other necessary tasks assigned by the Manager, Business Intelligence and Reporting.
